lead_paragraph: Annemiek van Vleuten suffered three fractured vertebrae and a concussion after a horrifying high-speed crash in the Olympic women's road race on Sunday but the Dutch rider said she will be fine and was more disappointed at missing out on a medal.

headline.print_headline: Cycling: I'll Be Fine, Says Van Vleuten After Horror Smash
